@*
    Primary app navigation (40.2) — the persistent surface switcher.
      • < 640px: a fixed bottom tab bar (icon-over-label), one tab per surface.
      • ≥ 640px: a slim left rail (icon-first column) with the account control docked at its foot.
    NavLink applies `.active` + aria-current="page" itself; /rooms uses prefix match so /rooms/{id}
    keeps Rooms lit. The account dropdown is rail-only — on mobile the Account tab is the entry point.
*@
<nav class="nav-shell" aria-label="Primary">
    <a class="skip-link" href="#main">Skip to content</a>

    <div class="nav-items">
        <NavLink class="nav-item" href="rooms" Match="NavLinkMatch.Prefix">
            <Icon Name="rooms" />
            <span class="nav-label">Rooms</span>
        </NavLink>
        <NavLink class="nav-item" href="library" Match="NavLinkMatch.All">
            <Icon Name="library" />
            <span class="nav-label">Library</span>
        </NavLink>
        <NavLink class="nav-item" href="account" Match="NavLinkMatch.All">
            <Icon Name="account" />
            <span class="nav-label">Account</span>
        </NavLink>
    </div>

    @* Desktop rail only (hidden < 640px, where the Account tab covers identity + sign-out). *@
    <div class="nav-account">
        <AccountMenu />
    </div>
</nav>
